The paper deals with the problem of detecting fraud in accounting data using deep autoencoder neural networks. This involves the use of machine learning techniques to analyze large-scale datasets, which is a common theme in the computer science subfields of cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Given the focus on deep learning and anomaly detection, cs.CR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.DB, and cs.IR.
